: Communication logs between you and other Individual Users
If you voluntarily choose to use this function, we process this information to enable you to communicate with other Individual Users.
We process this data as a processor on the Company User’s and your behalf.
Client function:
Client User’s user information (name, profile photo, gender, mobile number, user ID, gender and company), communication logs between Individual Users, Company Users and Client Users in group chats, information contained in electronic forms filled out by you, and votes.
We process this data as a processor on the Company User’s and your behalf.
We process this data as a processor on the Company User’s and your behalf.
Company information provided by you
(e.g., the company, invoice title, personal message, landline number, email address, position, title level, title, department, fax number, office seat and other information relating to the Company User or assigned by the Company User to you), an Individual User’s personal tagline that can be seen by other users and
any other information submitted by the Company User (e.g., organizational directory)
We use this information to enable you to use the Service.
We process this data as a processor on the Company User’s and your behalf.
Customer moments
: the information / media that you share, which may include geo-tagging your location (supported by Tencent Maps)
We facilitate the posting of information /media with other users.
Necessary to perform our contract with you to provide the Service where you seek to use our Customer Moments function
Chat Data
: Content of communications between you and another user or group of users, this would include your display name, email address, phone number, gender, location information (this involves sharing of your location supported by Tencent Maps), company and object of the chat. This information is stored on your device and the devices of the users that you have sent communications to.
We do not permanently store this information on our servers and it only passes through our servers so that it can be distributed to the users you have chosen to send communications to.
We facilitate the posting of your communications with other users.
Necessary to perform our contract with you to provide the Service where you seek to use chat services.
Live Broadcast data
:
Name, avatar, conference subject, audio and video data, audio and video quality data such as volume, packet loss rate and other relevant data and chat data.
We use this information to optimize compatibility and to ensure this meets your personalized requirements.
We process this data as a processor on the Company User’s and your behalf.
Meeting data
:
We collect the following data from you when you use this function: audio and video data (including any screen sharing which is encrypted and can only be viewed in real time), any shared files (documents that can be viewed and edited before, during or after the meeting)
Audio and video quality data (including volume, packet loss rate and other relevant data) and meeting log records on participants, time and duration of the meeting)
Communication log: meeting ID, meeting subject, meeting start and end time.
Network status data, being the status of your WiFi/internet connection and whether you have authorisation to connect to the Service and its network (this will not be collected by us).
Network status data, being the status of connection between your connecting server and the Service’s server (this will be collected and stored by the Service).
Blocked meeting participants (User ID of the blocked participants).
You instruct us to use this information solely to facilitate you using the Meetings function. We do not access the contents of your communications, which are encrypted.
We process this data as a processor on the Company User’s and your behalf.
WeChat data
:
We automatically collect certain data from you when you use WeChat (including when you access the Mini Programs or share your location with other users). For more information about the data we collect, please refer to the WeChat
